{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_59","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba docs/pipeline_notes.md | sed -n '180,290p'\"","aggregated_output":"   180\tMilestone 8A now reserves one explicit visual-stimulus discovery surface under\n   181\tthe versioned contract `stimulus_bundle.v1`.\n   182\t\n   183\tThe library-owned default layout is:\n   184\t\n   185\t- `data/processed/stimuli/bundles/<stimulus_family>/<stimulus_name>/<parameter_hash>/stimulus_bundle.json`:\n   186\t  authoritative stimulus descriptor and replay metadata\n   187\t- `data/processed/stimuli/bundles/<stimulus_family>/<stimulus_name>/<parameter_hash>/stimulus_frames.npz`:\n   188\t  optional cached frame stack derived from the descriptor\n   189\t- `data/processed/stimuli/bundles/<stimulus_family>/<stimulus_name>/<parameter_hash>/stimulus_preview.gif`:\n   190\t  reserved optional animation slot; the current local recorder marks it as skipped\n   191\t- `data/processed/stimuli/bundles/<stimulus_family>/<stimulus_name>/<parameter_hash>/preview/index.html`:\n   192\t  static offline preview report\n   193\t- `data/processed/stimuli/bundles/<stimulus_family>/<stimulus_name>/<parameter_hash>/preview/summary.json`:\n   194\t  machine-readable preview summary\n   195\t- `data/processed/stimuli/bundles/<stimulus_family>/<stimulus_name>/<parameter_hash>/preview/frames/frame-<index>.svg`:\n   196\t  deterministic preview frame images\n   197\t- `data/processed/stimuli/aliases/<alias_family>/<alias_name>/<parameter_hash>.json`:\n   198\t  compatibility alias record pointing old names at the canonical bundle\n   199\t\n   200\tContract notes:\n   201\t\n   202\t- bundle paths, metadata serialization, alias paths, and discovery now live in\n   203\t  `flywire_wave.stimulus_contract` rather than ad hoc script code\n   204\t- the descriptor metadata records the stimulus-contract version, design-note\n   205\t  version, canonical stimulus family/name, deterministic seed, RNG family,\n   206\t  parameter snapshot, parameter hash, spatial frame, temporal sampling, and\n   207\t  luminance convention\n   208\t- the default representation family is `hybrid_descriptor_plus_cache`:\n   209\t  descriptor metadata is authoritative and frame caches are optional\n   210\t- the shipped Milestone 8A recorder emits static offline preview sidecars\n   211\t  alongside the reserved GIF asset slot so preview inspection stays local and deterministic\n   212\t- timing is always expressed in milliseconds with `sample_hold` frame playback\n   213\t- the canonical spatial frame is `visual_field_degrees_centered` with origin at\n   214\t  the aperture center, positive azimuth to the right, positive elevation up,\n   215\t  and pixel centers as sampling points\n   216\t- luminance is always interpreted as linear values in `[0.0, 1.0]` with neutral\n   217\t  gray `0.5`; signed contrast parameters are deltas relative to that neutral\n   218\t  gray\n   219\t- compatibility aliases may rename stimulus family/name, but they may not\n   220\t  mutate seed, timing, spatial frame, luminance semantics, or generator\n   221\t  parameters\n   222\t\n   223\tThe practical replay key is the tuple `(contract_version, stimulus_family,\n   224\tstimulus_name, parameter_hash)`. Later manifests and tooling should resolve\n   225\tstimuli through the library contract instead of hardcoded frame filenames.\n   226\t\n   227\t`docs/stimulus_bundle_design.md` is the authoritative Milestone 8A decision\n   228\tnote; later tickets should cite it instead of re-litigating the representation\n   229\tfamily, replay semantics, or coordinate/luminance conventions.\n   230\t\n   231\t### Retinal input bundle contract\n   232\t\n   233\tMilestone 8B now reserves one explicit retinal-input discovery surface under\n   234\tthe versioned contract `retinal_input_bundle.v1`.\n   235\t\n   236\tThe library-owned default layout is:\n   237\t\n   238\t- `config.paths.processed_retinal_dir/bundles/<source_kind>/<source_family>/<source_name>/<source_hash>/<retinal_spec_hash>/retinal_input_bundle.json`:\n   239\t  authoritative retinal descriptor and replay metadata\n   240\t- `config.paths.processed_retinal_dir/bundles/<source_kind>/<source_family>/<source_name>/<source_hash>/<retinal_spec_hash>/retinal_frames.npz`:\n   241\t  optional sampled-frame archive derived from that descriptor\n   242\t\n   243\tContract notes:\n   244\t\n   245\t- bundle paths, deterministic retinal-spec hashing, metadata serialization, and\n   246\t  artifact discovery now live in `flywire_wave.retinal_contract` rather than\n   247\t  ad hoc script code\n   248\t- bundle identity is the tuple `(contract_version, source_kind, source_family,\n   249\t  source_name, source_hash, retinal_spec_hash)`\n   250\t- the bundle records an explicit upstream `source_reference` so later tooling\n   251\t  can trace the retinal recording back to the canonical stimulus or scene that\n   252\t  produced it\n   253\t- `retinal_input_bundle.v1` freezes one canonical frame meaning:\n   254\t  dense `time x eye x ommatidium` arrays with explicit eye order and stable\n   255\t  eye-local ommatidial indexing\n   256\t- the default and only supported v1 representation family is\n   257\t  `direct_per_ommatidium_irradiance`; eye-image rasters and higher-level\n   258\t  feature maps are downstream derived views rather than the source-of-truth\n   259\t  contract\n   260\t- timing is always expressed in milliseconds with `sample_hold` semantics\n   261\t- detector values use linear irradiance in `[0.0, 1.0]` with neutral `0.5` and\n   262\t  signed contrast interpreted relative to that neutral point\n   263\t- the coordinate block records one canonical right-handed world, body, head,\n   264\t  and eye frame convention so later scene, simulator, and UI work do not\n   265\t  silently disagree about orientation\n   266\t- the sampling-kernel block records the realized acceptance model, support\n   267\t  radius, normalization, and out-of-field fill behavior needed for\n   268\t  deterministic replay\n   269\t\n   270\t`docs/retinal_bundle_design.md` is the authoritative Milestone 8B decision\n   271\tnote; later tickets should cite it instead of re-litigating the retinal\n   272\tabstraction family, coordinate frames, or what one retinal frame means.\n   273\t\n   274\t### Offline coupling inspection contract\n   275\t\n   276\tMilestone 7 now also defines one deterministic offline inspection workflow for\n   277\tedge-level coupling review:\n   278\t\n   279\t- `scripts/08_coupling_inspection.py` reads the local synapse registry, one or\n   280\t  more edge bundles, the matching root-local anchor maps, and whichever local\n   281\t  geometry artifacts are needed by the realized anchor types\n   282\t- output goes to `config.paths.coupling_inspection_dir/edges-<sorted-edge-slug>/`\n   283\t- the report is static: `index.html`, `report.md`, `summary.json`, `edges.txt`,\n   284\t  per-edge detail JSON, and SVG panels for presynaptic readout plus\n   285\t  postsynaptic landing geometry\n   286\t- each edge emits compact `pass`, `warn`, `fail`, or `blocked` QA flags for\n   287\t  mapping coverage, anchor-map consistency, component integrity, cloud\n   288\t  normalization, and delay sanity\n   289\t- the detail JSON keeps the metric table, blocked-synapse rows, and aggregate\n   290\t  component rows in a review-friendly format so regressions can be asserted in\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
